TopicTitle: No refund for returning Exotic Minerals from Minmus mining

Articles.Content:
Hi,

After a great deal of effort, I set up a Kolony on Minmus.

There are 3 objectives:

  • learning the ropes about kolonies in order to deploy one on Duna
  • obtaining fuel
  • getting additional funds from mining

Last night I finally returned a probe full of Exotic Materials gently landing in water at 30 Km from KSC.
Although the Mission Summary screen acknowledged the return of parts and  resources, I didn't get the funds for the Exotic Minerals.

Is this normal?

https://imgur.com/a/iRHY5tL

Technical info:

  • KSP version 11.2 (can't upgrade to version 12 because Space Station are wobbling again as if Kerbal Joint Reinforcement - Next wouldn't work correctly).
  • List of mods:

Do Exotic Minerals actually have value? If you fill a tank with them in the VAB/SPH does it add to the total cost of the craft?

If they do, did you get a refund for everything else in that craft as normal, or did the refunds for other things also not work properly/at all?

23 minutes ago, jimmymcgoochie said:

Do Exotic Minerals actually have value? If you fill a tank with them in the VAB/SPH does it add to the total cost of the craft?

If they do, did you get a refund for everything else in that craft as normal, or did the refunds for other things also not work properly/at all?

Yes, they have an assigned value.
If you fill a tank, it does add to the cost of the craft (and a LOT).

Regarding the last 2 questions, I noticed that I don't get a full refund even for stock parts (e.g. I launch a Mk1-3 Command Pod and I lose funds after the recovery).

@Kazvan recovery rates do decrease as the distance from the KSC increases (to simulate the costs of actually sending a vehicle of some sort out to pick it up and take it back) but it shouldn’t give negative values for stock parts.

Can you create a CKAN mod pack with all your mods in it and post that here? I can use that to try and replicate the issue.
Looks like the stock bug that KSP recall fixes?

14 hours ago, modus said:

Looks like the stock bug that KSP recall fixes?

Thank you, this is the fix for the problem!
